## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3c0d-104">A propriedade ou campo deve ser público.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3c0d-104">The property or field must be public.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3c0d-105">A classe que contém a propriedade deve ser marcada com o <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementEntityAttribute> atributo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3c0d-105">The class that contains the property must be marked with the <xref:System.Management.Instrumentation.ManagementEntityAttribute> attribute.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3c0d-106">Quaisquer campos ou propriedades na classe que não estão marcadas com esse ou outro atributo de extensões do provedor WMI não serão instrumentadas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3c0d-106">Any fields or properties in the class that are not marked with this or another WMI Provider Extensions attribute will not be instrumented.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c3c0d-107">O exemplo a seguir mostra como usar o atributo ManagementConfiguration para marcar uma propriedade.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3c0d-107">The following example shows how to use the ManagementConfiguration attribute to mark a property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c3c0d-108">Essa propriedade é exposta ao WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c3c0d-108">This property is exposed to WMI.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Use the ManagementConfiguration attribute to specify that a property  
// is a read/write property in the provider. Consumers will be  
// able to get and set this property value through WMI.  
[ManagementConfiguration]  
public double ReadableWritableProperty  
{  
    get { return this.propertyValue; }  
    set { this.propertyValue = value; }  
}  
```
